      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIVIA UMIKO (2) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 2.25 lengths at this track in a handy 29.90 beating MYOLA THALIA. Has good early burn and is drawn to be prominent. Well placed and can measure up. MEPUNGA INFRARED (5) missed the frame last time but had been racing well prior to that, winning a Grade 5 three back before a placing at this track the following run. Safe beginner but tricky box to overcome. Expected to bounce back to best. MYOLA THALIA (4) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind RIVIA UMIKO (30.07) in a Other. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Expected to be in this for a long way. OREGON CALDWELL (1) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
